solution: Since $11 < 11.1 < 12$ we have $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor = 11.$  Next we have that  $2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor = 2 \lfloor 5.55 \rfloor = 2 \cdot 5 = 10.$ Therefore, $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor + 2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor = \boxed{21}.$
model_solution:
Step 1: Evaluate the expression inside the first floor function: $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor = 11.$
Step 2: Evaluate the expression inside the second floor function: $\lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor = \lfloor 5.55 \rfloor = 5.$
Step 3: Calculate $2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor$ and add $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor$ to it: $2 \cdot 5 + 11 = 21.$
Step 4: The expression $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor + 2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor = 11 + 21 = 32.$ Final Answer
